cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for understanding stories and extracting temporal relationships between events. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses neural network-based models and contextualized word embeddings, which are common techniques in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves comparative studies and analyses, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
